\section{Interviews}
%who are we going to interview in order to obtain the proper information on the system?
%do we interview the final user? the managers? the analysts?


Several interviews were carriedout to collect information about the system. The following were the main targets for our interview.

\vspace{5mm} %5mm vertical space

Managers: Since managers are the most responsible individuals in the company, interviewing them was helpful to understand  the overall structure of the company's system and the main goals. It also gives us  the big picture about the requirements for the database system  additional know on how to satisfy the customer demand.

\vspace{5mm} %5mm vertical space

IT technicians: the technicials handle the main part of the system and they manage daily to secure the availablity of the whole system. Each and every machine need routine maintanance and check up as well as update to satisfy the requirments.

to clarify the current technical infrastructure to enable the integration of the planned database system, define the constraints of the prevailing systems, and articulate the prerequisites for compatibility.

\vspace{5mm} %5mm vertical space

Employees in front line: Employees who support customer in various ways throughout the supermarket provide valuable insights into the customer experience and day-to-day operations. They can also provide information when customer need.

\vspace{5mm} %5mm vertical space

Customers (Users): Customers provide valuable feedback on their shopping experience, including product selection, pricing, customer service and their satisifaction.  Therefore conducting surveys with users  and focusing on them were very important.